<title>USA: Bank of Boston Corp Q4 net, shr rise.</title>
<headline>Bank of Boston Corp Q4 net, shr rise.</headline>
<dateline>BOSTON 1997-01-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>1996			1995</p>
<p> Shr primary		$1.26		    $1.09</p>
<p> Shr diluted		 1.24		     1.08</p>
<p> Net			201,500		  180,300</p>
<p> Avg shrs diluted     155,157		  157,959</p>
<p>	  12 MONTHS</p>
<p> Shr primary		$3.99		    $4.17</p>
<p> Shr diluted		 3.93		     4.09</p>
<p> Net			650,200		  678,300</p>
<p> Avg shrs diluted     156,112		  156,768</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: Results reflect acquisition of BayBanks on July 29, 1996.  </p>
<p>Q4 1996 includes gain of $47 million for sale of 20 branches to US Trust Corp, $25 million charge from transfer of about $400 million of commercial real estate loans into a held-for-sale account, and credit losses of about $15 million.</p>
<p>Q4 1996 also includes valuation-related charge of $11 million associated with certain investments, and $6 million charge for vesting of stock price performance.</p>
